new_version_errors.3.0.16:
The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '3.0.16' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - could not hash URL template 'https://pypi.io/packages/source/p/psycopg-c/psycopg-c-{{ version }}.tar.gz'

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "psycopg" %}
{% set version = "3.1.7" %}
{% set build_number = 0 %}

package:
  name: psycopg-split
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  - folder: psycopg
    url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/p/psycopg/psycopg-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: 83bb8b231a58802b6434d994d20c4897818d7e2d8970206975a06b6919c63985

  - folder: psycopg-c
    url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/p/psycopg-c/psycopg-c-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: 3be083c911780d98a9ccc61059b104cdbc3121e6f038feb5e6fa82418c6cb004

build:
  number: {{ build_number }}

requirements:
  host:
    - python
  run:
    - python

outputs:

  - name: psycopg-c
    script: install_psycopg-c.sh  # [linux and py<=38]
    build:
      number: {{ build_number }}
      script: cd psycopg-c && {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv  # [not linux or py>38]

    requirements:
      build:
        - {{ compiler('c') }}
        - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
        - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
        - postgresql                             # [build_platform != target_platform]
      host:
        - python
        - pip
        - postgresql
      run:
        # libpq is a repackaging of only the library to connect to postgres
        - libpq
        - python
    test:
      commands:
        - pip check
      requires:
        - pip

  - name: psycopg
    build:
      number: {{ build_number }}
      script: cd psycopg && {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

    requirements:
      build:
        - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
        - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
        - postgresql                             # [build_platform != target_platform]
      host:
        - python
        - pip
        - backports.zoneinfo  # [py<39]
        - postgresql
        - typing-extensions  # [py<38]
        - tzdata  # [win]
      run:
        - python
        - {{ pin_subpackage('psycopg-c', max_pin='x.x.x.x.x.x') }}
        - backports.zoneinfo >=0.2.0  # [py<39]
        # libpq is a repackaging of only the library to connect to postgres
        - libpq
        - typing-extensions >=4.1
        - tzdata  # [win]

    test:
      imports:
        - psycopg
        - psycopg.pq
        - psycopg_c
      commands:
        - pip check
      requires:
        - pip

about:
  home: https://psycopg.org/psycopg3/
  summary: PostgreSQL database adapter for Python
  description: |
    Psycopg 3 is a newly designed PostgreSQL database adapter for the Python
    programming language. Psycopg 3 presents a familiar interface for everyone
    who has used Psycopg 2 or any other DB-API 2.0 database adapter, but allows
    to use more modern PostgreSQL and Python features.
  license: LGPL-3.0-or-later
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  doc_url: https://www.psycopg.org/psycopg3/docs/
  dev_url: https://github.com/psycopg/psycopg/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - msarahan
    - ocefpaf
    - xylar
